Detailed Description

A PyModel is a Scene Node with an animation player, an action queue and the ability to attach models to hardPoints.

A PyModel provides script access to a SuperModel.

PyModels do a lot of other cools things too.

PyModelBase extends Aligned, so we don't have to

void PyModel::move ( float  dTime  )  [virtual]

This method gives models a chance to move during entity tick.

We can't move during scene tick because our movement might put us in a different node which would stuff up all the iterators. And it's nice to have all of these movements done at once.
